co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.partitioned

Class TransactionalPartitionConsumer

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.lib.partitioned.TransactionalPartitionConsumer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PartitionConsumer

    @Beta
public final class TransactionalPartitionConsumer
extends Object
implements PartitionConsumer
    An implementation of PartitionConsumer that uses a Transactional to execute its methods in a new transaction. For each call to the methods it implements, it starts its own, new transaction.

      • onFinish

        public void onFinish(List<? extends Partition> partitions,
            boolean succeeded)
        Description copied from interface: PartitionConsumer
        This method must be called on any partitions returned by the #consumePartitions method. If a program fails to call this method for any partitions, those partitions will be 'expired' after a timeout defined on the configured ConsumerConfiguration.
        Specified by:

        succeeded - whether or not processing of the specified partitions was successful
